</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a high plank position with your hands a bit wider than shoulder-width apart on the floor.</li>



<li>Keep your body straight from head to heels throughout the entire movement.</li>



<li>Bring your body towards the floor by bending your elbows while pointing them downwards.</li>



<li>Push back up to the starting position by fully extending your arms.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core tight; avoid sagging or arching your back during the reps.</li>



<li>Try to bring your chest as close as possible to the ground.</li>



<li>Focus on achieving a <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/sms.14006#:~:text=Conclusion-,Full%20ROM%20resistance%20training%20is%20more%20effective%20than%20partial%20ROM%20to,full%20and%20partial%20ROM%20interventions%20to%20generate%20changes%20in%20muscle%20architecture.,-1%20INTRODUCTION" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">full range of motion</a> for maximum benefit from each rep.</li>



<li>Modify by performing push-ups on your knees if needed until you build strength.</li>



<li>Breathe steadily; exhale as you push up and inhale as you lower down.</li>
</ul>



