</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Reverse Grip Chair Inverted Rows Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Position yourself under a sturdy table or desk, gripping the edge with palms facing you.</li>



<li>Extend your legs, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels.</li>



<li>Pull your chest up towards the edge of the table, keeping elbows close to your body.</li>



<li>Lower yourself back down with control.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged throughout the movement to maintain a straight body line.</li>



<li>Squeeze your shoulder blades together and down at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>To make it easier, bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground.</li>



<li>For added difficulty, elevate your feet on a chair or stability ball.</li>
</ul>



