<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best Full-Body Circuit Routine For Thanksgiving</h2>



<p>If you want to create a complete workout with the exercises discussed, we’ve done the work for you. You can complete all eight exercises, but doing just five is sufficient. Targeting all body parts will effectively burn fat and work your muscles.</p>



<p>For this workout, it’s best to perform it in a circuit style. In this method, one exercise is performed after another, with minimal rest between each exercise, completing one round each. After finishing a round, take a short rest, around 90 seconds, before starting the next round.&nbsp;</p>



<p>You can do this workout up to three times per week, with one day of rest in between each workout. The rest day can include a walk, which will help you recover actively.&nbsp;</p>



<p>These last-minute workouts for Thanksgiving will give you the bang for your effort and burn some serious calories.</p>



